{
  "texts": [
    "Features that have a long persistence interval (d ib i) are considered to be likely to reflect the true topological features of the underlying manifold M.",
    "These features are represented in the PD by points far away from the diagonal.",
    "A short persistence interval describes a feature that is possibly generated from noise or is otherwise insignificant.",
    "Features with short persistence will be represented by points close to the diagonal line in the PD.",
    "Hence, points in the PD that are further away from the diagonal are considered more informative than those that are closer to it."
  ]
}